				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: lvl 53 bard needs advice <a name="8016"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 10 03 3:41 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>No thats not what is meant by swarm kite.  What you are referring to is chant kiting.  Also you should add a fourth chant (or even a fifth one) if you are going to do that.  Look below for what they are talking about...
<br />

<br />
Swarm kite steps:  
<br />
1. Get just proximity aggro on a BUNCH (AKA swarm) of social mobs (Mobs that will assist one another when under attack)
<br />
2. Charm 1 of them.
<br />
3. Have your pet attack one of the swarm
<br />
4. Pet gets OWNED in a hurry when attacked by the swarm
<br />
5. Invis to break charm, timed for when pet is at about 10% health.
<br />
6. Chant the last 10% or so off your ex-pet, get XPs 
<br />
7. If there is another mob nearby to aggro, do it, to keep the swarm fed
<br />
8. go to step 2
<br />

<br />
You can exceed a kill a minute in some places with this method.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
