				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: lvl 53 bard needs advice <a name="8488"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 24 03 7:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At lvl 53 I went to PON and never left.  
<br />
Just to the left of Grave Yard in PON is a area with alot of trees and only one spawn off in one corner.  Its easy to just run around in circles there after you've pulled a mob.  I recommend the evil trees as they have the best money drops.  When you get to a lvl you don't like the return you're getting from the trees, learn how to run over to the hobgoblin camp accoss the river (doing it wrong gets you dead or pulling a train that often kills the folks at hobgoblin camp).  In between hobgoblin and hedge is a nice open area that has no spawns.  From there you can pull these nettling wraiths and chant kite them.  They move really fast compared to other mobs but really slow compared to bards!  Or if hobgoblins is empty you can pull those mobs single and kite them down.  They drop beautiful gems and good vendor items. Just opposite the nettling wraith area is a large hill you can't get up on, but you can float out and target these lvl 62 gloom nightmares (2 of em anyway) that are up on the hill and pull them with your dot songs.  They take a while to kill but the exp is really nice.  I went to 61 in a short amount to time.  
<br />
</span></td>
